subject: Add processors table missing properties
commitMessage:
Add processors table missing properties

- Add following missing properties: Name, Spare part number,  Model,
Processor type, Processor architechure, Version, Health rollup,
Asset tag, Min speed MHz, Max speed MHz, Total cores, Total threads,
Instruction set, Identify Led

- Design of the table has been updated

- Waiting for the following to be merged to test the Identify Led:
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/37045

Signed-off-by: Sandeepa Singh <sandeepa.singh@ibm.com>
Change-Id: If6eeb3b0afea6510f7ea53e2d66cbf1d123b3217

Change has been successfully merged by Derick Montague

I noticed there are some new properties in the API. Do we want to add them?

InstructionSet": "PowerISA",
"ProcessorArchitecture": "Power",
"Status": {
"State": "Absent"
},
"TotalCores": 12,
I think we can remove this since they will all be the same value.
Yes, makes sense to remove something repetitive 😊. Let's take insights from the design team as well.
I am referring to the sortable option being set to true.
This is going to be the same for all these sections. I am wondering if we should use a mixin so if we wan to change, it only needs to be changed in one place.
Sure Derick, this can be done.
I have replied to Sukanya in her story. Can the two of you coordinate

Can we remove the inline margins and add them to the section-divider ruleset? That will make the margins consistent. I have already found that they are different between this story and the BMC manager story.

I have changed the UI of BMC manager table and included margins in the section divider ruleset. Now it
can be used for all tables of hardware page. 😊
Can we format hardwaretype as hardwareType to meet our naming conventions? 😊
It's a best practice to name the file the same name as the selector. Can you change the file name to _section-divider?
This should be the name you use for the file name. :)
CCIN is not used outside of IBM
Why are we renaming the SparePartNumber, fruNumber?
As per discussion with Santosh, fruNumber should be mapped to SparePartNumber.
Total cores is not coming as part of API response, we have checked in -20.
Don't think we should call this CCIN
Why was this added? Line 394 is "Status (Health rollup)"
There is a possibility that this might be used by other tables on the hardware page.😊
There is not much difference between the two. We just need identifyLed only, as that is what we will be showing in the GUI. Will be removing indicatorLed. 😊
TotalCores is still a valid property..
Also if you removing something, please state that in the commit msg.
Total cores is still a valid I need to add it in the GUI again. Also there are few more properties coming waiting on them and then I'll update it. 😊
Can I ask why we are waiting if we know what the properties are? If we know what they are, can we add them and the value will be -- until they are available.
We can add them but the design needs to be changed as there are some five new properties. Lets discuss this in today's status call.
Not sure hardwareType makes a lot of sense. For processors it will be something like "cpu 0"/"cpu 1" or "CPU 0"/"CPU 1"
Its been decided that we'll be showing 'Name' as 'name' instead of 'hardware type' on the webui.

instead of adding margin right we can add padding to the table details row. Th9is way this section-divider can be reused outside of the table section.

I would add   padding-right: calc(50px + (#{$table-cell-padding} * 2));  below line 61 in _tables.scss
and remove line 4 above

instead of adding margin top and bottom here, maybe it would be better to use bootstrap utilities on the section dividers in the table, or maybe create another class here specifically to add margin top & bottom to expand row details row. I think that will keep the section divider style more reusuable outside of the expanded table row
Was a little unsure on hardware type, do we want to remove it completely from the page as of now?

"turning... off" will not translate well. Using enable/disabled would be better terms to use

      "errorDisableIdentifyLed": "Error disabling Identify LED.",
      "errorEnableIdentifyLed": "Error enabling Identify LED."

Will we remove the v-if/else when all the backend location indicator active stories are merged? (Question for the team, I don't remember if we talked about it and if it will be removed later we may want to open a story)
Just a info, if you are keeping sm="6", spacing will start from min width(sm) mentioned upto max width, so if you want you can skip xl="6".
Right now code for identify led has not been merged, so to show up '--' until we have it merged. I was planning to remove it in separate story so that at least this story can be merged.
Maybe leave a comment saying will be removed when backend changes merged
Yes, leaving a comment in code 😊
